      "comment": "THE SWIFT ONE (5) produced a far better performance when second up last start, leading from this barrier and fighting well to go under by a neck as runner-up at this circuit and distance. Should strip fitter again so can go one better. SHAZADELE (3) raced in a handy position last start and boxed on for third, less than 6m behind THE SWIFT ONE. That was the fourth time in a row she has placed at this venue. Draws well enough to play a role again. GO WITHOUT (10) draws on the back row but is looming as a threat after a good effort last start, finishing third at Penrith. ROCKIN IN PARADISE (4) was just behind SHAZADELE last start and came from wider than this when he won three back at this circuit and distance.",
